(30, 4, 6, '30.jpg', 'IMPORTANT UPDATE - Tips on smashing UNN Post Utme', '\n<p>\n   As we count down the months, you will notice that, we have not less than 3 months towards UNN post utme examination. And there are some tips you need to know very well in the course of preparing for the very examination. These tips include:\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   1. Nature of the examination : This is the most complicated issue facing many aspirants every year. Someone might be reading and studying quite right but not in the area of examination concentration. Some even study NECO and WAEC past questions while preparing for the very post utme examination without knowing they are missing the road. Now, ask your self, how exactly does UNN post utme examination looks like?... Does it covers some o level past questions?... Do they repeat questions from past questions?... What are the exactly cogent reading materials that are suitable for preparation of UNN post utme examination???...  And many more questions you need to be asking your self concerning the nature of the examination... Self interrogation is part of learning because through that, you will get to the pathway of resolving your problems. So, the greatest threat and cause of most aspirants\' failure is the lack of knowledge concerning the nature of the examination they are preparing for. Now, based on the subheading, an answer to this trauma is studying jamb past questions.... When I said, studying jamb past questions, I didn\'t mean that you should go and cram the answers; you are being advised to study with understandings and be able to answer a similar question anywhere found. Know it that the nature of UNN post utme examination is 70% jamb past questions, 20% general knowledge on the four subjects you are writing and 10% UNN post utme past questions....\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   To be continued.... \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Don\'t forget to hit the like button. And also leave your comments in the comment box for future analysis...\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Best regards!!! \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   From: Lionel Richard Nnabuike\n</p>\n', '2018-04-18 07:57:21', 0, 'APPROVED', 154557),
